content.description: Power endurance route with lots of fun crimps! Pretty steep!
content.location: Route to the right of In Between Days, and left of Drive by trucker. Much of the climbing stays in the dark black streak in the wall.

content.description:
In your face right off the ground. Begins to let up after the fixed draws.

A long and fun trip.
content.protection:
10-ish bolts to rappel rings. 2 fixed draws.

60m rope will get you down
content.location: 2nd from the right. look for 2 fixed chain draws about 30' up.

content.description: Another classic South park route. Powerful from the start to finish.
This route traverses the low roof in a series of powerful underclings, then plumblines straight for the anchors.
Steep start with big moves and some underclings lead to the crux, which involves some big brick pinches to a precise move to a pocket.
content.location: This route is to the right of Government shutdown, and left of temptation. So this route is second from the left, as noted by Sam.

content.description: Fun route that starts off with some funky, thuggy moves to the fourth bolt and a decent rest, and then finishes with some fairly easy but techy, sloper moves to the top. Really fun to the sixth bolt but quality diminishes after that.
content.protection: 8? bolts to anchors. Stick clipping first two bolts highly recommended. Be careful clipping third bolt.
content.location: Furthest route left on the Epoxy Wall. First route to the right of Hippy Digger and left of Inbetween Days

content.description: Powerful, bouldery route that stay on ya til the chains. Super fun!!
content.protection: bolts. There is a fixed draw on the 2nd or third bolt.
content.location: Just right of Drive by Trucker. The route with the fixed draw on the lower section.

content.description:
Sustained and powerful but with good holds. Virtually straight up and slightly overhung until the final few moves.

Bring some lock-off strength and endurance and prepare for a rad time!

Caution - belaying from the log is a good way to catch a choss-bomb right on the dome.

climbs.name: Don't Forget to Bring a Towel (or Harness)

content.description:
Begin on the start holds of Chef's Meatballs (far right route on the wall) and traverse left crossing Scuzzlebutt, Mr. Hankey, and Ricardo to the end of the traverse at the long grass underneath the start of EDS. Watch for loose rocks, but there are no necessary holds above the first bolt of any route. The route is a grade or two harder when traversing left to right (EDS --> Chef's Meatballs).

Feel free to try it and let me know if I'm completely wrong about the grade. Or, you could just remember to bring your harness and climb the routes with bolts...
content.location: Far right side of South Park area.

content.description: This route is very sustained and quite a fight for .10d.
